content:
This chunk discusses a shortcut method in Panda3D for loading textures as models, which automatically creates a textured card, situated within a broader discussion on applying textures to 2D or 3D scenes.

cpp

As a special shortcut, you can also directly load the texture as though it were a model, which will automatically create a card for it:

NodePath card;
card = window->load_model(window->get_render(), "maps/noise.rgb");

This short piece of code will result in a single polygon in the scene with the noise texture applied to it. Of course, if you need it in the 2-D scene, you should use ~WindowFramework::get_aspect2d() or ~WindowFramework::get_render2d() instead of ~WindowFramework::get_render().
